==English==

===Noun===
'''rut'''  (''plural:'' '''[[ruts]]''')
# Sexual desire or oestrus of deer, cattle, and various other mammals.
# [From Old French: route, way, pass, road] A furrow, groove, or track worn in the ground, as from the passage of many wheels along a road.
# A fixed routine, procedure, line of conduct, thought or feeling. (See also [[Rutter]])

